						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the courtyard of the Añjanēyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, (no date).</p>						

						<p>States that Aḷiya-Rāmappaya, having made a representation to the king and obtained his consent, granted the village Aligera to the temple of Chennakēśava for a feeding house for the itinerant <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇas</hi> and <hi rend="italic">śūdras</hi> who resorted to the military road.</p>						

						</summary>
